        <headline>Flash Flood Warning issued June 13 at 10:17AM EDT until June 13 at 12:00PM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 1017 AM EDT, Doppler radar and automated rain gauges indicated
thunderstorms producing heavy rain extending from Ravenel and Adams
Run to Bennetts Point, moving northeast at 20 mph. Between 4 and 6
inches fell earlier today and flooding is likely ongoing in some
areas. The risk for more flooding may increase as these storms move
through with additional amounts up to 1 inch possible.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...Radar and automated gauges.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Johns Island, Hollywood, Meggett and Yonges Island.
</description>
        <instruction>Be aware of your surroundings and do not drive on flooded roads.

Report flooding directly to the Charleston National Weather Service
at 1-888-383-2024 or email your reports to nws.charlestonsc@noaa.gov.</instruction>
